Spain Has ‘Cushion’ to Absorb Airports, Lottery Delays: Salgado

-- B y   C h a r l e s   P e n t y
-- 
2011-10-14T12:35:19Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-10-14/spain-has-cushion-to-absorb-airports-lottery-delays-salgado.html
Spain  has a sufficient “cushion”
to absorb the impact of delays in the receipt of revenue from
the sale of airport conessions and a stake in the state lottery
company, Finance Minister  Elena Salgado  said at a news
conference in  Madrid  today.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Charles Penty at 
 cpenty@bloomberg.net  